      • addVectorLines

        public Completable addVectorLines(List<usdk.printer.line.Line> lines)
        Add vector lines.

        Used to add many lines(> 100 lines) to printer.

        if need reverse print or under line text,TextLine convert to Bmp image.

        Examples: 

              Printer printer;
      printer = Printer.getInstance();
      VectorPrinting.init(Printer.getPaperWidth());
      List lines = new ArrayList<>();
      VectorFormat format = new VectorFormat(24);
      format.lineSpace = 2;
      //设置反白打印
      format.isReversePrint = true;
      //设置下划线
      format.isUnderLineText = true;
      TextLine textLine = new TextLine("ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz1234567890@反白打印",format);
      lines.add(new ImageLine(textLine.generateBmpImage()));
      printer.addVectorLines(lines)
                 .doOnComplete(() -> Printer.getInstance().cutPaper(true))
                 .andThen(Printer.getInstance().print())
                 .test()
                 .await()
                 .assertComplete();

        Parameters:
        lines - lines.
        Returns:

      • addVectorText

        public void addVectorText(String text,
                          usdk.printer.VectorFormat format)
                   throws DeviceException
        Add vector text with config.

        If the text is too long in one line, it can be auto wrapped. Also you can use \n or call the interface multi times to split lines.

        support reverse print、under line text.

        Examples: 

              Printer printer;
      printer = Printer.getInstance();
      VectorPrinting.init(Printer.getPaperWidth());
      VectorFormat format = new VectorFormat(24);
      format.lineSpace = 2;
      format.isUnderLineText = true;
      printer.addVectorText("ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz1234567890@下划线", format);
      printer.cutPaper(true);
      printer.print();

        Parameters:
        text - text.
        format - format.
        Throws:
        DeviceException - device exception.
